result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Kevin Maurice Carter Jr

records.addlTxt: Order for Defendant to be Transported FORTHWITH

Defendant Kevin Maurice Carter Jr in court, in custody.  Attorney Arial Jade Rosenberg in court for Kevin Maurice Carter Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Claire E Zyber in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
BRANCH 41, JUDGE SKWIERAWSKI for  BRANCH 10, JUDGE HAVAS.
Case in court for competency hearing.  Parties in receipt of examiner's report. State does not challenge Dr. Collins report.  Defendant does challenge Dr. Collins report.  Court qualified Dr. Collins to testify as an expert in the field of psychology.   Sworn for the State:  Dr. Deborah Collins  Testimony closed.  Arguments heard. After review of all evidence, report and testimony of Dr. Collins Court finds the defendant lacks substantial capacity to understand court proceedings or to assist in his own defense.  Court orders proceedings suspended.   Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame. Order of Commitment signed and filed.  Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department for transportation to the designated facility. FORTHWITH. 
Court orders case adjourned  back to Branch 19 for Competency Review Hearing
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for November 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
BRANCH 10 IN JURY TRIAL CASE SPUN TO BRANCH 41. Parties all notified.

Attorney Colin Patrick McGinn in court on behalf of Attorney Arial Rosenberg, defendant Kevin Maurice Carter not in court, in custody.  Claire E Zyber appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
HEARING HELD VIA ZOOM/LIVE ON DACAST.  Case in court for return on doctor's report.  Parties reviewed report filed by Dr. Collins on 7-13-2022.  Defense contests the findings of the report and requests a hearing date.  Court set date as requested.  This matter will be held in person in room 504 of the Courthouse.  Case adjourned to Branch 10.  Competency hearing scheduled for August 30, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Forensic evaluation ordered.  INITIAL APPEARANCE NOT HELD.  Trial court to address INITIAL APPEARANCE.

Defendant Kevin Maurice Carter in court with attorney Maryann Corea. Defendant Kevin Maurice Carter in custody.  Katrina Amy Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Kevin Maurice Carter appeared by video means with Attorney.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Havas, Branch 10. Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
